Sets the value of an environment variable. This only changes the environment value in this process, not system-wide. This uses some hackery to work, and may not be 100% reliable in all cases, and shouldn't be relied on heavily. It will always work with get_env, however, so you can rely on that mechanism. The value will always be interpreted as a string, so if you are expecting a particular data type on a call to get_env, you will need to manually cast the variable. Arrays will be toString'd as well, but will be accepted.
